The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 08 June is 278,452 (32,093.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 03 June, there were 744 new confirmed cases (85.8 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 27 May, there were 599 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 24% (145 extra cases).
